  "texts": [
    "In this case, two attributes, namely \"being a woman\" and \"taking care of children\" are correlated and both can have detrimental effects on salary.",
    "Attempting to address bias solely based on gender may unintentionally disadvantage certain minority groups, such as women without caregiving responsibilities or men who do have such responsibilities.",
    "Hence, when considering mitigation strategies, side effects on different subgroups should be carefully analyzed.",
    "Beyond its legal challenges (see Sect.",
    "\"AI biases, discrimination and unfairness\"), intersectionality is currently actively addressed also by technical research (Gohar & Cheng, 2023) and Science and Technology Studies (van Nuenen et al., 2022)."
